text: I'm always on the lookout for new turkey
sandwich ideas because it is one of my
go-to healthy sandwiches and this one
features one of my favorite members of
the fall produce lineup a bright green
tart apple start by slicing a granny
smith apple just remove the core and
just make thin slices Granny Smith not
only have a tremendous amount of vitamin
C and fiber they add a really nice tangy
fresh note so I have two slices of
toasted whole-grain bread add a little
whole-grain mustard you could also use
regular Dijon now a lot of people add a
tremendous amount of mayonnaise to
turkey sandwiches I'm a fan of
mayonnaise but I'm also a huge fan of
hummus and sandwiches
how much adds a nice creaminess you
don't have any of the saturated fats you
had a little protein boost it also helps
hold everything together which I love in
a sandwich now to this add a couple of
leaves of fresh lettuce layer in our
apples definitely have apples on the
mind we just recently had another really
delicious Apple recipe the vanilla bean
baked apples so tasty this is a great
one using the raw nice and crunchy add a
couple of slices of turkey Turkey is one
of those great lean proteins to use in
sandwiches make you feel full all day
love that final touch a little slice of
aged cheddar this is probably my
favorite part of the sandwich cheddar
just goes so nicely with hummus Turkey
green apples everything looking good
let's give it a slice now this is a
turkey sandwich
hmm
thumbs up this is a super delicious
sandwich couldn't be easier thrown
together in no time hope you enjoy it
